1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 12]

23
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:36,330
Mom.

24
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:37,850
You can lose anything else,

25
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:38,820
but not your passport.

26
00:01:39,950 --> 00:01:42,100
I know. It's not my first time
traveling abroad.

27
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:44,570
Think it through before you buy anything

28
00:01:44,590 --> 00:01:45,380
over there.

29
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,570
Be careful.

30
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,690
Yeah, I got it.

31
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,180
I need to go check in now.

32
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,660
Ms. Zhang and the others
have already gone in.

33
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:51,900
Let's go!

34
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,290
Alright, son.

35
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:03,540
Just

36
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,330
get back to work.

37
00:02:04,510 --> 00:02:04,820
Alright.

38
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,380
Come here, give me a hug.

39
00:02:06,950 --> 00:02:08,290
I'm too old for hugs.

40
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:09,890
Doesn't matter. You're still my son.

41
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:12,570
Mr. Guo.

42
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:14,260
Tao.

43
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,260
This must be your mom, right?

44
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,170
Yes, my mom.

45
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,460
Hello, ma'am.

46
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:21,580
I'm a friend of Guo Cong's.

47
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,610
My name's Shen Taotao.

48
00:02:22,710 --> 00:02:24,170
- Nice to meet you.
- Where are you headed?

49
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:26,930
Bangkok, with a few friends.

50
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:28,930
The 8:40 flight?

51
00:02:28,950 --> 00:02:29,580
That's the one.

52
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,060
You're on that flight too?

53
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,610
What a coincidence. Same flight!

54
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:33,130
That's great!

55
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:34,180
I'm the purser on that flight.

56
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,060
If you need anything, just let me know.

57
00:02:36,080 --> 00:02:36,650
Sure.

58
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:37,380
Guo Cong,

59
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,610
now you can stop worrying.

60
00:02:38,630 --> 00:02:40,060
I'll take good care of your mom.

61
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:41,170
Don't bother.

62
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,130
She can take care of herself.

63
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,410
Oh, stop it.

64
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:46,540
I'll come find you if I need anything.

65
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,450
Tao,

66
00:02:47,470 --> 00:02:48,820
just call me Tao.

67
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:49,290
Alright.

68
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:51,010
Guo Cong, get back to work.

69
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,170
I'll take your mom to check in.

70
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:52,660
Okay.

71
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,940
Thanks, I appreciate it.

72
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,410
Oh, one more thing.

73
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:57,380
Don't keep ordering takeout
while I'm gone.

74
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,170
You hear me?

75
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,570
Make some noodles, fry an egg,
something simple and clean.

76
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:01,170
I know.

77
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,540
Alright, let's go.

78
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,170
Sure.

79
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:04,060
Take care of yourself.

80
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,130
Don't worry.

81
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:17,540
Ma'am,

82
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:19,290
your suitcase is overweight.

83
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:21,220
Could you please take a few things out?

84
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:22,780
Really?

85
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,010
One second.

86
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:25,450
Of course.

87
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,100
Tao.

88
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:27,940
What should I do?

89
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,540
She says my suitcase is overweight.

90
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,890
I've already taken so much out.

91
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:32,130
I can't take anything else out.

92
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:34,610
Don't worry. Let me handle this.

93
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:35,980
Just wait here for me, okay?

94
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,690
You sure you can handle it?

95
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,500
No problem.

96
00:03:37,710 --> 00:03:38,220
Okay.

97
00:03:41,470 --> 00:03:43,410
Hi, I'd like to upgrade this passenger.

98
00:03:43,430 --> 00:03:44,260
I'll pay for it.

99
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:53,940
All set.

100
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,500
- Thank you. - No problem at all.

101
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,380
All done, ma'am.

102
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,260
That was fast!

103
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,540
Thank you.

104
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:01,410
My pleasure.

105
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:02,220
Shall we head in?

106
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:04,220
Let's go.

107
00:04:08,470 --> 00:04:09,060
Ma'am,

108
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:10,290
I brought you a blanket.

109
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:11,660
Oh, thank you.

110
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:12,980
Tao,

111
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:13,660
well…

112
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,780
tell me,

113
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:16,410
how did I go

114
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,140
from economy to first class?

115
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:19,930
Well, here's what happened.

116
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:20,660
I managed to get you

117
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,930
a complimentary upgrade.

118
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:25,700
Thank you so much, Tao.

119
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,410
Oh,

120
00:04:26,430 --> 00:04:28,580
did you pay that overweight fee for me?

121
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,730
Here, let me transfer it to you.

122
00:04:29,950 --> 00:04:31,610
Ma'am, there wasn't any extra fee.

123
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,460
With a first-class ticket,

124
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,290
your luggage isn't overweight at all.

125
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,370
Nothing to worry about.

126
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,540
Really?

127
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:40,980
Lucky I ran into you!

128
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,220
Thank you so much, dear.

129
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,490
Ma'am, let me know if you need anything.

130
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,610
I promised Guo Cong I'd look after you,

131
00:04:46,630 --> 00:04:47,900
and I always keep my word.

132
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,170
I'll go get you something to eat.

133
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,220
Thank you.

134
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:51,980
Just a moment.

135
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:42,490
Boss.

136
00:05:42,870 --> 00:05:43,540
I'm here.

137
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:44,610
Sit.

138
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:47,980
Just you?

139
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:50,340
Of course it's just me.

140
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,250
I mean,

141
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:53,780
you know everything about me.

142
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,490
No point taking
that kind of risk, right?

143
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,610
Besides, I'm just a nobody.

144
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:58,580
Who'd even notice me?

145
00:05:59,160 --> 00:05:59,930
What do you want to eat?

146
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:01,020
My treat.

147
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,140
No need, Boss. I'm good.

148
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,020
Don't bother.

149
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:06,700
Call me Mr. Long from now on.

150
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,610
All this 'Boss' stuff

151
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:09,780
makes me sound like some gangster.

152
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:11,730
Listen,

153
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,460
the noodles here are really good.

154
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,340
Excuse me.

155
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:19,250
One dry tossed noodle,
extra beef tendon balls.

156
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:20,490
Alright then,

157
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:21,780
thanks, Mr. Long.

158
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:22,460
Coming!

159
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,460
Tell me,

160
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:24,810
what have they got you doing lately?

161
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:28,340
That Qian guy,

162
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,610
they don't need me on him anymore.

163
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,250
Now they've got me
tailing a customs officer.

164
00:06:31,270 --> 00:06:33,850
Name's Guo… Guo Cong.

165
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,100
Why are they watching him?

166
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,100
I… I have no idea.

167
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:42,850
The guy's a customs officer.

168
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,250
No way I'm going anywhere
near the airport.

169
00:06:45,390 --> 00:06:46,540
There are cameras everywhere.

170
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:47,100
So I've been

171
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:49,660
waiting downstairs by his apartment,

172
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,850
seeing what he does off duty.

173
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:53,900
Just watching him?

174
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:55,050
Just watching.

175
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,730
These customs officers

176
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:05,250
are nothing like that Qian guy.

177
00:07:06,430 --> 00:07:07,460
They're always on the lookout.

178
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:12,370
Change your clothes often,
and switch your rides.

179
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,410
Mr. Long,

180
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,780
you've got to be kidding me.

181
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:18,780
Look at me,

182
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,220
how can I get all these different cars?

183
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:23,490
Then walk more.

184
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:24,610
Drive less.

185
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,920
[Transfer to Chen Weipeng
Amount 2,000]

186
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,160
[WeChat Pay…]

187
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,020
I'm sending you two grand.

188
00:07:42,510 --> 00:07:43,370
Take a cab if you need to.

189
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:47,460
Mr. Long!

190
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,980
What are you doing?

191
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,220
I'm working for you.

192
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,370
You're being way too generous.

193
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,170
You're working for me,

194
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,100
so I need the job done right.

195
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,610
This is nothing.

196
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,490
Get this done,

197
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,490
and there's more waiting.

198
00:08:00,390 --> 00:08:01,290
Mess it up,

199
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:02,100
same deal,

200
00:08:05,270 --> 00:08:06,410
I'll wipe out your family.

201
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:12,410
One more thing.

202
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:13,810
Wherever

203
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,340
Guo Cong is,

204
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,490
whatever he's doing,

205
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,140
report to me immediately.

206
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:19,780
Of course!

207
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,810
Relax. I've got it covered.

208
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:21,700
Cheers.

209
00:08:21,830 --> 00:08:22,340
Cheers.

210
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:55,120
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs
Auction of Seized Raw Amber – Lot 1]

211
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:55,940
Raw amber?

212
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,900
[Shameless customs officers seized
these amber stones from me last week.]

213
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,040
[They stop us from bringing things in,
then sell them themselves.]

214
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,120
[New Year is coming.
Customs is lining up their bonuses.]

215
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,060
[They confiscate goods just to
make money for themselves. Disgusting.]

216
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:04,040
[Outrageous! They confiscate our stuff
and then auction it off?]

217
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:05,650
What a load of nonsense.

218
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:09,060
You trolls really think
you can just smear Customs like that?

219
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,060
What are you saying?

220
00:09:11,870 --> 00:09:12,530
Nothing.

221
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,580
A bunch of people online
are trashing Customs.

222
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:15,490
Watch me clap back.

223
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:17,340
Somebody needs to educate them.

224
00:09:22,670 --> 00:09:23,610
Ms. Strawberry,

225
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,180
we persuade people with facts,
not attitude.

226
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:29,180
Fine, facts it is.

227
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:39,960
[L Strawberry Jam Follow]

228
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:40,920
[Followed Successfully]

229
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,820
You're still arguing with those trolls?

230
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,420
Look.

231
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:49,300
Those influencers

232
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:52,100
I've been reporting
for selling luxury goods online.

233
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,420
During their livestreams,

234
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,340
they claimed everything was
imported from overseas.

235
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:57,610
I checked their shipment volume,

236
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:58,770
and the numbers are huge.

237
00:09:58,960 --> 00:09:59,730
This is serious.

238
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:02,130
That's basically open smuggling.

239
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,340
They've got a lot of nerve.

240
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:06,730
So I reported every single one of them.

241
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:08,980
If they think they can
pull that right under my nose,

242
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,700
I'll make sure they pay for it.

243
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:12,010
Well done.

244
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,890
Can't let them get away with that.

245
00:10:13,910 --> 00:10:14,650
Exactly.

246
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:17,060
Time to

247
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,940
get my beauty sleep now.

248
00:10:26,030 --> 00:10:26,650
What's wrong?

249
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:28,460
- Something fell? - My badge.

250
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,180
I got it.

251
00:10:30,550 --> 00:10:32,650
- Here you go. - Thanks, shero.

252
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,180
Don't mention it.

253
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,820
Isn't this the watch

254
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,250
we saw in that watch magazine last time?

255
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:11,820
Yep.

256
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,980
It's already been released in Europe.

257
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,010
Serial number 001.

258
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:18,890
It was auctioned
for nearly 800,000 euros,

259
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:20,530
and bought by a Chinese buyer.

260
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:21,890
Mr. Guo,

261
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,460
12 o'clock.

262
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,850
The guy in the black cap.

263
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:27,770
Looks like one of the buyers
from that luxury watch launch.

264
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:31,370
But today he's dressed way too casually.

265
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:33,460
He doesn't look like someone who'd spend

266
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,460
800,000 euros on a watch.

267
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:45,700
Maybe he's trying to
avoid being recognized.

268
00:11:46,670 --> 00:11:47,460
Qiang.

269
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:48,770
Come to the diversion post.

270
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,300
Hello, China Customs.

271
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:52,700
Please cooperate with our inspection.

272
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:53,850
Inspection for what?

273
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,060
Your watch.

274
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:00,370
This way.

275
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,220
Mr. Guo.

276
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,650
The watch box in his suitcase is empty.

277
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,370
Please come with me.

278
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:24,770
Bowen,

279
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:25,580
special inspection room.

280
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:30,610
Your watch, please. Thank you.

281
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:34,300
What is it?

282
00:12:34,390 --> 00:12:36,010
Is there something wrong with the watch?

283
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,130
Beautiful watch.

284
00:12:37,870 --> 00:12:38,890
Just looks nice.

285
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:39,770
Not worth much.

286
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:40,610
Mr. Zheng,

287
00:12:40,630 --> 00:12:42,490
you're being far too modest.

288
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,890
This is the original box for this watch.

289
00:12:57,270 --> 00:12:58,300
Richard Mille.

290
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,770
Released in 2007.

291
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,250
RM011.

292
00:13:02,790 --> 00:13:05,180
Automatic movement, RMACU caliber.

293
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,980
A very classic tonneau-shaped case.

294
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,180
If I'm not mistaken,

295
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,530
the market price

296
00:13:09,550 --> 00:13:11,300
is around 1.49 million yuan.

297
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,300
You really know your watches.

298
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:15,220
I don't know any of that stuff.

299
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,850
I just thought it looked nice.

300
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,530
I happened to see it
while I was shopping.

301
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:22,250
Looked expensive, caught my attention,
so I remembered it.

302
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:23,810
But Mr. Zheng,

303
00:13:23,830 --> 00:13:26,210
this watch exceeds
the duty-free allowance.

304
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,820
If you didn't declare it
when you left the country,

305
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:31,020
then duties must be paid
when you re-enter.

306
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:33,540
I didn't know
there was a rule like that.

307
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:33,940
Yes.

308
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:35,540
I honestly had no idea.

309
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:36,130
Well,

310
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:38,130
since it's over the duty-free limit,

311
00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:39,410
handle it however you need to,

312
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:40,820
just follow the rules.

313
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,980
Per regulations, the tax rate is 50%.

314
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:44,250
That much?

315
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:44,700
Yes.

316
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,500
Of course, there is another option.

317
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,660
You can apply for return shipment.

318
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:48,730
I'll process the return.

319
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:49,930
Alright.

320
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:51,050
Bowen,

321
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,050
help Mr. Zheng
process the return shipment.

322
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:56,410
Oh, Mr. Zheng,

323
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,020
the return process may take a while.

324
00:13:59,070 --> 00:13:59,980
Are you traveling with anyone else?

325
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:00,980
If so, you should let them know.

326
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:04,660
No.

327
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,020
I'm traveling alone.

328
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:07,260
Alright.

329
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:07,900
This way, please.

330
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:08,450
Goodbye.

331
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:09,220
Goodbye.

332
00:14:20,870 --> 00:14:22,180
The man I just took
to the special inspection room,

333
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,340
the one in the black cap.

334
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:23,940
You remember him?

335
00:14:24,670 --> 00:14:25,130
Yes.

336
00:14:25,390 --> 00:14:26,420
Change into plainclothes.

337
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,530
Two things:

338
00:14:27,870 --> 00:14:28,980
Go to the return shipment counter

339
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,340
and check

340
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:32,060
whether he sends the watch box back too.

341
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:32,980
Second,

342
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,530
if he makes a call,

343
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,130
try to find out who he's talking to.

344
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:37,610
Yes, sir.

345
00:14:37,790 --> 00:14:38,300
Go.

346
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,120
RETURN SHIPMENT

347
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:50,940
Hello?

348
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:52,770
How's it going?

349
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,060
You got through smoothly?

350
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,010
Don't even ask.

351
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:56,770
Listen,

352
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:57,730
don't wait for me.

353
00:14:57,750 --> 00:14:58,490
Get in the car.

354
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,100
Once I finish handling this return,

355
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:00,980
I'll head straight back to the office.

356
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,220
You owe me a big bonus for this one.

357
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:05,700
That one watch alone
cuts out hundreds of thousands in tax.

358
00:15:05,910 --> 00:15:08,490
Flip it for a markup,
we pocket another hundred grand.

359
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:09,370
That's a huge profit.

360
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:10,420
Uh…

361
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:11,980
[Liu Cheng]
I'm so sorry!

362
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:12,790
[Liu Cheng]

363
00:15:12,790 --> 00:15:13,580
[Liu Cheng]
Is your phone okay?

364
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:14,340
Sorry, sorry!

365
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,010
Did I break it?

366
00:15:16,030 --> 00:15:17,100
I'm really sorry.

367
00:15:17,180 --> 00:15:17,850
I just…

368
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:19,300
I was in a rush.

369
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:20,580
Everyone's waiting for their turn.

370
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:21,340
It's no use getting impatient.

371
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:22,180
You're right.

372
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,060
I'm so sorry.

373
00:15:24,910 --> 00:15:25,370
Hey.

374
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:26,610
It's fine.

375
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,250
[Liu Cheng]
Someone knocked my phone down.

376
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:29,490
[Liu Cheng]
Go ahead.

377
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:34,890
Find anything?

378
00:15:35,390 --> 00:15:36,530
Our old friend

379
00:15:36,550 --> 00:15:38,130
was indeed on the same flight
as Zheng Ting.

380
00:15:38,150 --> 00:15:39,530
But according to airport surveillance,

381
00:15:39,550 --> 00:15:40,610
he already left by car.

382
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:42,300
Timed it perfectly.

383
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:43,420
So what do we do now?

384
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,650
Hand it over to Anti-Smuggling?

385
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:46,100
Zheng Ting won't admit it.

386
00:15:46,270 --> 00:15:47,940
Liu Cheng has already cleared Customs.

387
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,340
He's probably already
passed the watch off.

388
00:15:49,910 --> 00:15:51,420
Even if we notify Anti-Smuggling now,

389
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:52,890
it'll be hard for them to trace it.

390
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:54,850
What's your plan?

391
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:59,250
What's wrong with you guys?

392
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,370
Why am I being brought back here again?

393
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:03,820
Mr. Zheng, please calm down.

394
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:04,730
Because of

395
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,610
the empty watch box in your luggage.

396
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:07,580
What about the box?

397
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:08,980
Didn't you already check it?

398
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,730
When you processed the return,

399
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:12,180
why didn't you return the watch box too?

400
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:14,340
I liked the box.

401
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,650
What's wrong with keeping it?

402
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,460
You're gonna charge tax on the box?

403
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:19,820
The problem is, this box and your watch

404
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:20,770
aren't a matching set.

405
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:22,700
Your watch was released in 2007,

406
00:16:22,790 --> 00:16:24,220
but this box is from this year.

407
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,180
That's a good one, officer.

408
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,300
Richard Mille boxes are standardized.

409
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:30,130
How could you tell what year it's from?

410
00:16:30,280 --> 00:16:30,940
Mr. Zheng,

411
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:32,420
maybe you're not aware,

412
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:33,130
but you're not the first person

413
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:34,820
to bring this model through Customs.

414
00:16:35,150 --> 00:16:35,730
Over the years,

415
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:37,530
we've seen cases like this

416
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:39,340
far more times than you'd imagine.

417
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,370
As far as we know,

418
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:42,180
Richard Mille's box supplier

419
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,980
was changed two years ago.

420
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,490
The previous supplier was in Europe,

421
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,420
and the current one
is in Southeast Asia.

422
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:49,890
The boxes may look almost identical,

423
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,730
but because of differences
in temperature and humidity,

424
00:16:51,870 --> 00:16:52,730
the newer boxes

425
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,940
are slightly darker in color
than the older ones.

426
00:16:56,870 --> 00:16:58,370
I really didn't know that.

427
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:06,700
Mr. Zheng,

428
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,140
how do you

429
00:17:09,350 --> 00:17:10,220
explain this photo?

430
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:15,460
Look at me.

431
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:16,460
Sorry about that.

432
00:17:17,030 --> 00:17:18,090
I honestly forgot.

433
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,250
I did leave

434
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:21,620
that watch overseas with someone
holding it for me.

435
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:22,770
As for the box,

436
00:17:22,790 --> 00:17:24,090
I really liked it.

437
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,180
So I kept it with me.

438
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,900
That's not against the law, is it?

439
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:28,530
Alright.

440
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:30,660
I've finished the return process.

441
00:17:31,070 --> 00:17:31,940
If there's nothing else,

442
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:32,700
I'll be on my way.

443
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:33,900
Do you know Liu Cheng?

444
00:17:38,110 --> 00:17:39,220
I'm sorry?

445
00:17:39,790 --> 00:17:40,530
I'm not sure I follow.

446
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,860
Liu Cheng is a local professional mule,

447
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:45,620
well known in that circle.

448
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:47,770
We've dealt with him plenty of times.

449
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:48,940
You could say he's an old acquaintance.

450
00:17:49,350 --> 00:17:50,380
In this line of work,

451
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:51,730
people like him usually

452
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:53,140
don't use real names with clients.

453
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,090
But they still need to
build a name for themselves.

454
00:17:56,790 --> 00:17:57,460
So they can

455
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:58,940
get more business.

456
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:01,460
[Passenger Registration Form]
Liu Cheng's real name is Yan Haidong.

457
00:18:01,460 --> 00:18:02,030
[Passenger Registration Form
Yan Haidong]

458
00:18:02,030 --> 00:18:03,900
'Liu Cheng' is the name
he uses with clients.

459
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,770
In other words,

460
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,860
if he contacted you using that name,

461
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,290
then chances are,
you're one of his clients.

462
00:18:12,070 --> 00:18:12,730
Mr. Zheng,

463
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:15,090
haven't I made myself clear enough?

464
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:17,380
I'm sorry,

465
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:19,770
but I honestly have no idea
what you're talking about.

466
00:18:20,270 --> 00:18:22,050
Article 67 of the Criminal Law

467
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:23,330
of the People's Republic of China,

468
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:24,620
paragraph three, states:

469
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:25,980
A suspect

470
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:27,620
who truthfully confesses their crime

471
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,420
may receive a lighter sentence,

472
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:33,140
and may be given a mitigated penalty

473
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:35,420
if any especially serious consequence

474
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,330
is avoided due to their confession.

475
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:50,770
Alright.

476
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,220
I admit it.

477
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,250
That watch,

478
00:18:54,590 --> 00:18:55,380
I bought it.

479
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:57,860
I just forgot

480
00:18:58,520 --> 00:18:59,460
to pay the duties.

481
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,330
You chose to come clean

482
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:03,660
instead of covering it up.

483
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:06,250
I'm very glad you made that choice.

484
00:19:06,510 --> 00:19:08,010
And I can promise you,

485
00:19:08,270 --> 00:19:09,860
you won't regret it.

486
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:11,290
Let's go.

487
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:23,730
Zheng Ting's case is more than

488
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:25,010
just unpaid duties.

489
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:27,660
He coordinated with
Liu Cheng beforehand,

490
00:19:27,790 --> 00:19:29,140
with a clear intent to smuggle.

491
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:30,530
Smuggling a high-value luxury watch

492
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:32,180
and evading a large amount of taxes

493
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:33,860
clearly constitutes suspected smuggling.

494
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,330
Anti-Smuggling will take it from here.

495
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:49,010
Ma'am,

496
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:50,380
what would you ladies like to drink?

497
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:52,330
It's okay, Tao.

498
00:19:52,350 --> 00:19:53,700
Go take care of your work.

499
00:19:53,780 --> 00:19:55,090
No need to keep fussing over me.

500
00:19:55,550 --> 00:19:57,050
Don't worry, ma'am.

501
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:58,980
How about some warm orange juice?

502
00:19:59,110 --> 00:20:01,010
I'll warm it up for you. Just a moment.

503
00:20:01,790 --> 00:20:03,490
And what would you like, ma'am?

504
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:05,220
I'll have the same.

505
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:07,010
Of course. Just a moment.

506
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:14,460
That young lady

507
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:16,770
has her eye on your son.

508
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,700
Really?

509
00:20:20,590 --> 00:20:21,620
I know

510
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:22,660
what I'm seeing.

511
00:20:29,270 --> 00:20:30,050
Tao,

512
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,010
why are you flying with us today?

513
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:34,980
I swapped shifts with Hua today.

514
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:37,290
I've got a friend on this flight.

515
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:39,530
The lady waiting for the orange juice?

516
00:20:39,550 --> 00:20:40,290
Who is she?

517
00:20:40,550 --> 00:20:41,730
Mr. Guo's mom.

518
00:20:42,830 --> 00:20:44,660
Wow, Tao,

519
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:46,620
already winning over
your future mother-in-law?

520
00:20:47,070 --> 00:20:48,250
Stop talking nonsense.

521
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:49,940
Just helping take care of her for him.

522
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:53,380
"Helping take care of her", huh?

523
00:20:53,510 --> 00:20:54,730
Did he ask you to do that?

524
00:20:59,160 --> 00:20:59,700
Ladies,

525
00:21:00,070 --> 00:21:00,980
careful.

526
00:21:01,110 --> 00:21:02,050
- Thank you. - Thank you.

527
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:02,860
Enjoy.

528
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:04,250
Let me know if you need anything.

529
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,050
Ms. Zhang,

530
00:21:22,070 --> 00:21:23,180
you go on ahead.

531
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,010
My son's on duty,
so I'm going to see him.

532
00:21:25,070 --> 00:21:26,460
Alright, I'll head out then.

533
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,090
Oh,

534
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:29,090
that jade you bought

535
00:21:29,110 --> 00:21:30,220
costs over 5,000 yuan.

536
00:21:30,310 --> 00:21:32,700
Make sure you go through
the declaration channel.

537
00:21:32,830 --> 00:21:34,330
I know, you're such a nag!

538
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,380
Now go see your son!

539
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:37,290
Okay, bye!

540
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:44,220
Excuse me.

541
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:45,770
Hello. China Customs.

542
00:21:45,790 --> 00:21:47,380
Please cooperate
with a baggage inspection.

543
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:48,770
Me?

544
00:21:49,270 --> 00:21:49,860
Yes.

545
00:21:50,270 --> 00:21:51,330
Please cooperate.

546
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:53,700
Ma'am, what's going on?

547
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,700
She wants to inspect my things.

548
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,770
Are you checking her? Know who she is?

549
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:01,010
Like I said,

550
00:22:01,030 --> 00:22:01,900
no matter who she is,

551
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,330
everyone has to cooperate
with customs inspections.

552
00:22:04,310 --> 00:22:05,010
Fine.

553
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,140
I'll go with you.

554
00:22:12,510 --> 00:22:13,980
Bowen, cover for me.

555
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:23,530
Easy, Tao.

556
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:24,380
I'm fine, ma'am.

557
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,140
It's heavy.

558
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:28,220
Alright.

559
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,380
See for yourself.

560
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:33,530
No weapons, no explosives,
no explosive materials.

561
00:22:34,030 --> 00:22:36,810
No fresh fruits, vegetables,
or seeds either.

562
00:22:37,310 --> 00:22:40,010
And definitely no contraband or drugs.

563
00:22:40,310 --> 00:22:41,980
This cash, this bag,

564
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:44,530
and these cosmetics
are all for my personal use.

565
00:22:44,550 --> 00:22:45,730
Nothing over the limit.

566
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:50,980
Mr. Guo.

567
00:22:51,350 --> 00:22:51,900
All clear.

568
00:22:52,750 --> 00:22:53,730
Your mom's here.

569
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:01,730
Mom.

570
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:02,220
There.

571
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:03,620
What are you doing here?

572
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,010
Can't you see?

573
00:23:05,110 --> 00:23:06,620
I'm being inspected.

574
00:23:08,110 --> 00:23:10,220
You must've been looking around for me.

575
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:12,250
My colleague spotted
something suspicious.

576
00:23:12,270 --> 00:23:13,700
She had to stop you for inspection.

577
00:23:14,030 --> 00:23:14,810
You know how this works.

578
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:16,860
I do.

579
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:18,090
I get it.

580
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:19,810
So I'm cooperating fully.

581
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,220
Is there a problem?

582
00:23:21,510 --> 00:23:22,380
No problem at all.

583
00:23:23,350 --> 00:23:24,460
I'm sorry about this, ma'am.

584
00:23:24,830 --> 00:23:26,050
Don't apologize.

585
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:27,530
You're just doing your job.

586
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:28,330
Mom,

587
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:29,660
you must be tired.

588
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:30,660
Go home and rest.

589
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:31,940
Mr. Guo,

590
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:32,770
you get back to work.

591
00:23:32,790 --> 00:23:33,810
I'll walk your mom out.

592
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:34,770
Thank you.

593
00:23:35,550 --> 00:23:36,090
Son,

594
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:38,050
come home for dinner after your shift.

595
00:23:38,070 --> 00:23:39,860
I have something important to tell you.

596
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,250
I'll take that.

597
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,050
Head home early.

598
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:49,180
- Mr. Guo, I didn't know…
- Don't overthink it.

599
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:50,460
You did nothing wrong.

600
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:51,530
Get back to your post.

601
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:53,250
Got it.

602
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:00,860
Zhang Yu!

603
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,140
Zhang Yu!

604
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:03,180
Zhang Yu!

605
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:09,940
What was that all about?

606
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:11,180
Who was that lady?

607
00:24:11,310 --> 00:24:14,220
And why were both Mr. Guo
and Shen Taotao there?

608
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:17,900
That was Mr. Guo's mom.

609
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:19,530
You…

610
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:22,010
You stopped her?

611
00:24:23,350 --> 00:24:25,620
You have no idea how awkward that was.

612
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,860
And when I opened her suitcase,

613
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:29,420
I was terrified there'd be

614
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,730
something prohibited inside.

615
00:24:30,790 --> 00:24:33,180
Good thing she follows the rules.

616
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:35,220
But

617
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:37,050
how did Shen Taotao

618
00:24:37,070 --> 00:24:38,420
end up with Mr. Guo's mom?

619
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:39,730
How would I know?

620
00:24:41,070 --> 00:24:43,860
Hey, are you even listening to me?

621
00:24:45,790 --> 00:24:47,290
Forget it. I'm going back to my post.

622
00:24:51,240 --> 00:24:52,660
Something's going on.

623
00:25:16,590 --> 00:25:17,180
Mom.

624
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,010
You're back, son.

625
00:25:19,030 --> 00:25:19,620
I'm home.

626
00:25:23,070 --> 00:25:23,900
Making dumplings?

627
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:25,810
You should've told me earlier.

628
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:27,730
I could've come home sooner to help.

629
00:25:27,750 --> 00:25:29,010
Who needs your help?

630
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:31,290
I've got someone already.

631
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:36,490
Mom,

632
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:37,940
honestly,

633
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:39,660
you're getting younger by the day.

634
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:40,330
Cong!

635
00:25:40,350 --> 00:25:40,900
Hurry up,

636
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:41,810
put it down!

637
00:25:42,070 --> 00:25:42,490
Now!

638
00:25:42,510 --> 00:25:43,810
You're going to twist your ankle!

639
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:45,490
Oh, cut it out.

640
00:25:46,270 --> 00:25:47,290
Go wash your hands.

641
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:54,770
Tao.

642
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,660
Mr. Guo, you're back.

643
00:25:58,110 --> 00:26:00,090
Come on, you're off duty already.

644
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:01,700
Just call him by his name.

645
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:03,660
Sorry

646
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,010
for making you help out.

647
00:26:05,350 --> 00:26:06,460
Not at all.

648
00:26:07,550 --> 00:26:08,220
Ma'am.

649
00:26:11,790 --> 00:26:12,860
That was fast!

650
00:26:14,310 --> 00:26:15,940
Here, see if the seasoning's right.

651
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:21,250
Perfect.

652
00:26:22,590 --> 00:26:23,900
I didn't expect it, Tao,

653
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,290
you're actually quite capable.

654
00:26:25,590 --> 00:26:26,730
I learned from the best.

655
00:26:27,750 --> 00:26:29,010
I'll grab another pair of chopsticks.

656
00:26:35,790 --> 00:26:36,810
Mom,

657
00:26:37,110 --> 00:26:39,050
you invited her over and didn't tell me?

658
00:26:39,070 --> 00:26:40,290
What's this about?

659
00:26:41,110 --> 00:26:42,290
What's there to say?

660
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:44,460
This whole trip,

661
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:45,980
I had Tao taking care of me.

662
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:48,330
She looked after me on both flights.

663
00:26:48,550 --> 00:26:51,180
She even gave up her own time off

664
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,980
to spend almost a day showing me around.

665
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:56,090
Now that I'm back,
having her over for a meal,

666
00:26:56,110 --> 00:26:57,380
to thank her, what's wrong with that?

667
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:58,700
Dinner's fine,

668
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,050
but why is she helping
with all the housework?

669
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:01,810
We could've gone out. I'd have treated.

670
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:02,620
Alright, enough.

671
00:27:02,790 --> 00:27:04,660
Nothing beats eating at home.

672
00:27:05,030 --> 00:27:06,810
Now go freshen up and come help.

673
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:07,420
Hurry.

674
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,140
But…

675
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:13,860
Here you go, Tao.

676
00:27:15,590 --> 00:27:16,490
An extra pair？

677
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:17,620
I didn't even notice.

678
00:27:19,110 --> 00:27:20,490
Look at yours, so beautiful.

679
00:27:21,270 --> 00:27:22,420
Now look at yours.

680
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,730
Wow, these look incredible!

681
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,620
Like little flowers!

682
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:31,420
Pretty girl, pretty dumplings.

683
00:27:37,790 --> 00:27:38,570
See you, Zhang Yu.

684
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:39,860
- Bye! - Bye.

685
00:27:46,510 --> 00:27:48,700
-Yu, I'm out. Bye. - Bye.

686
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:54,290
Zhang Yu,

687
00:27:54,350 --> 00:27:55,180
aren't you leaving?

688
00:27:56,550 --> 00:27:57,530
Are you free tomorrow?

689
00:27:57,790 --> 00:27:58,570
Tomorrow?

690
00:27:59,510 --> 00:28:00,380
Sure.

691
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,010
Why?

692
00:28:01,030 --> 00:28:02,460
Then come to an exhibition with me.

693
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:03,460
What kind of exhibition?

694
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:05,220
It's a photography exhibition

695
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:08,330
my mentor's uncle is putting on.

696
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:10,290
Did Mr. Guo ask you to go?

697
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:12,570
No, it's just…

698
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:15,220
This uncle is actually

699
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:17,220
Mr. Chen's old classmate.

700
00:28:17,510 --> 00:28:19,380
He basically watched Mr. Guo grow up.

701
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,620
When we were at
the nursing home that day,

702
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,700
he insisted Mr. Guo bring me along.

703
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:25,490
Well then,

704
00:28:26,030 --> 00:28:26,980
I'm not going there
to be the third wheel.

705
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,900
What? It's nothing like that.

706
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:29,420
Listen.

707
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,090
I won't know anyone there.

708
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,770
Mr. Guo will definitely be busy

709
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:35,290
chatting with all his friends.

710
00:28:35,310 --> 00:28:37,180
I'll just be standing there
awkward and bored.

711
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,250
Just come with me.

712
00:28:38,270 --> 00:28:39,860
Nope. I'm not being the third wheel.

713
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:40,530
Fine, how about this?

714
00:28:40,550 --> 00:28:41,770
We'll go get dinner after.

715
00:28:41,790 --> 00:28:42,700
I'll treat you to something nice.

716
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:45,660
Deal.

717
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:48,570
Guess I can reluctantly go with you.

718
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:50,250
My mentor did tell me to listen to you.

719
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:52,050
You're only saying yes
for the free meal.

720
00:28:52,830 --> 00:28:53,810
Go get changed.

721
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:55,010
Alright.

722
00:28:55,590 --> 00:28:56,620
See you tomorrow then.

723
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,860
Sweetheart, what are you doing?

724
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,570
You've made such a mess in here.

725
00:29:25,590 --> 00:29:26,330
Mom, don't touch anything.

726
00:29:26,590 --> 00:29:27,490
I'm not done trying things on yet.

727
00:29:32,110 --> 00:29:33,180
Are you going on a date?

728
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:35,770
Bring him home so I can meet him!

729
00:29:35,790 --> 00:29:36,460
Mom!

730
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:37,420
Why is that always

731
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:38,770
the first thing you think of?

732
00:29:39,270 --> 00:29:40,180
All you care about is

733
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:41,980
who I'm going with, what we're doing,

734
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,420
where we're going, whether it's a guy,

735
00:29:43,510 --> 00:29:44,420
and whether I'm dating someone.

736
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:45,460
Seriously,

737
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:46,530
can't I just go out with my best friend

738
00:29:46,550 --> 00:29:47,700
to shop and see an exhibition?

739
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:48,730
Of course you can!

740
00:29:48,750 --> 00:29:49,980
That's great.

741
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,460
Even better if that 'best friend'
happens to be a guy.

742
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:53,250
Mom!

743
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:55,420
Okay, okay.

744
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:56,180
Come here.

745
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:57,380
Look what I got you.

746
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:00,570
What is it?

747
00:30:00,830 --> 00:30:01,770
Open it yourself.

748
00:30:03,830 --> 00:30:05,420
Chaumet's Liens d'Amour!

749
00:30:06,510 --> 00:30:08,090
Isn't this your favorite necklace?

750
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:09,700
Your dad and I saw it the other day,

751
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:10,810
so we bought it for you.

752
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:13,490
- Thank you, Mom! - With your salary?

753
00:30:13,510 --> 00:30:14,660
No way you'd ever afford this.

754
00:30:15,830 --> 00:30:16,220
Mom.

755
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:17,700
Why bring up my salary right now?

756
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:18,420
So annoying.

757
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:19,770
Try it on!

758
00:30:20,790 --> 00:30:22,290
I need the perfect outfit to match it.

759
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:23,660
How about this one?

760
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:25,220
I was just thinking
this one looked good.

761
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:25,860
No.

762
00:30:26,350 --> 00:30:27,220
No?

763
00:30:27,550 --> 00:30:28,220
What about this?

764
00:30:28,310 --> 00:30:29,940
I think these colors
go perfectly with it.

765
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:32,180
Mom, that's it!
I have nothing left to wear!

766
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:33,490
Let's go shopping!

767
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:36,660
Zhang Yu!

768
00:30:37,550 --> 00:30:38,180
Zhang Yu!

769
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:39,010
Hurry!

770
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:40,250
Oh my gosh!

771
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:41,380
I'm exhausted.

772
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:43,530
Weren't we meeting at six?
Why are you here so early?

773
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:45,010
Early? Please.

774
00:30:45,030 --> 00:30:46,330
Someone needs to help you get ready.

775
00:30:46,350 --> 00:30:47,730
Get ready for what?

776
00:30:47,750 --> 00:30:50,180
It's just a photography exhibit.

777
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,290
Of course you need to get ready!

778
00:30:52,750 --> 00:30:54,860
We wear customs uniforms all year long.

779
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,330
We barely get chances to dress up.

780
00:30:56,440 --> 00:30:57,530
Gonna make the most of it.

781
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:00,050
I'll be fine with something simple.

782
00:31:00,070 --> 00:31:01,180
No, absolutely not.

783
00:31:01,510 --> 00:31:03,330
Trust my taste. I know what I'm doing.

784
00:31:03,830 --> 00:31:04,700
Let me take a look

785
00:31:04,830 --> 00:31:05,620
at your face.

786
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:11,530
Why does your skin look so dull lately?

787
00:31:12,830 --> 00:31:14,090
Have you been staying up late again?

788
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:16,220
And skipping your sheet masks?

789
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:20,180
I've told you so many times,
you can't keep doing this.

790
00:31:20,350 --> 00:31:22,530
Go wash your face first
and do your skincare properly.

791
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:26,010
Use this foundation as your base.

792
00:31:26,030 --> 00:31:27,570
And for those dark circles,

793
00:31:27,590 --> 00:31:29,770
use this orange concealer first,

794
00:31:29,790 --> 00:31:30,570
then go over it with this one.

795
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:31,090
Got it?

796
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:34,180
I'll put on some false lashes for you.

797
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:36,490
After that, we'll do your hair.

798
00:31:36,510 --> 00:31:37,290
That should do it.

799
00:31:38,680 --> 00:31:39,700
We can skip this one.

800
00:31:44,070 --> 00:31:45,660
What's all this?

801
00:31:45,960 --> 00:31:47,530
What am I supposed to wear then?

802
00:31:47,550 --> 00:31:48,900
I don't even need
to look in your closet.

803
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:49,460
Way too plain.

804
00:31:49,480 --> 00:31:50,620
I brought you a few options.

805
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,570
Next time we're both off,

806
00:31:52,590 --> 00:31:53,860
we're seriously going shopping.

807
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:55,330
You can't keep wearing my clothes.

808
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:56,420
That many?

809
00:31:57,110 --> 00:31:58,330
We need options.

810
00:31:58,590 --> 00:31:59,460
I'm telling you,

811
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:00,460
with a face this pretty…

812
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:00,940
What?

813
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,460
Are you talking about yourself?

814
00:32:02,830 --> 00:32:03,810
Now that's something I like to hear.

815
00:32:14,080 --> 00:32:18,360
[Chasing Dust]

816
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:28,980
Xiang, I'm heading out.

817
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,140
Sure, take care.

818
00:32:39,510 --> 00:32:40,980
You must be Mr. Xiang.

819
00:32:41,270 --> 00:32:42,220
Yes, that's me.

820
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:45,250
Sorry, and you are…?

821
00:32:45,590 --> 00:32:46,770
Hello, Mr. Xiang.

822
00:32:46,960 --> 00:32:48,250
I'm a friend of Guo Cong's.

823
00:32:48,270 --> 00:32:49,460
My name is Shen Taotao.

824
00:32:50,680 --> 00:32:51,530
Hello.

825
00:32:51,550 --> 00:32:52,290
Ms. Shen.

826
00:32:54,110 --> 00:32:55,730
Cong didn't mention you were coming.

827
00:32:55,750 --> 00:32:56,700
Well,

828
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:58,420
his mom asked me to stop by.

829
00:32:58,590 --> 00:32:59,180
She said

830
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,330
you're someone Guo Cong respects a lot,

831
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:04,290
and an outstanding photographer as well.

832
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:06,050
She told me
I should come learn from you.

833
00:33:06,310 --> 00:33:08,700
She really treats me like family.

834
00:33:08,790 --> 00:33:11,490
She even sent such a beautiful guest
to grace my little show.

835
00:33:11,590 --> 00:33:12,940
You're too kind.

836
00:33:14,110 --> 00:33:15,530
Has Guo Cong gotten here yet?

837
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,290
Haven't seen him yet.

838
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:21,010
I can tell you care about him.

839
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:23,420
Not at all, Mr. Xiang.

840
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:25,860
We just work at the airport together.

841
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:27,530
I'm a flight attendant.

842
00:33:28,510 --> 00:33:30,250
There's nothing wrong
with liking someone.

843
00:33:30,270 --> 00:33:31,090
No need to explain.

844
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:35,770
Somehow I feel like

845
00:33:36,030 --> 00:33:37,770
we've met somewhere before.

846
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:39,760
[Zhenyao Computers AMD & Gigabyte
Training Event]

847
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:42,330
Hello.

848
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:44,460
I took a photo of you.

849
00:33:45,350 --> 00:33:47,330
I'm with the Photographers Association.

850
00:33:47,330 --> 00:33:48,960
[President Xiang Xiuyuan
Binhai Photographers Association]

851
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,250
I remember now!

852
00:33:51,590 --> 00:33:54,900
One time outside the airport hotel,

853
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:56,220
you took a picture of me.

854
00:33:56,240 --> 00:33:57,700
